sentences.english: Also, stitch the edge of the window screen which is between the lower circle and the flank of the cone.
sentences.chinese: 同样，缝住底下的那个圈和圆锥侧面的纱窗边缘。

sentences.english: He looked through the screen and saw that Bill and Ted were in the back seat.
sentences.chinese: 透过纱窗，他看到比尔和特德坐在后排。

sentences.english: Living in the fifth floor of the Dama Wang said the most effective mosquito control is Shachuang.
sentences.chinese: 住在五楼的王大妈说防蚊最管用的是纱窗。

sentences.english: She doesn't hear the scratch of your putty knife as you pry open the screen.
sentences.chinese: 你用油灰刀慢慢撬开纱窗，她依然熟睡着。

sentences.english: Insolation wind screens to shake Fei, Chun Hong Lo hand swab things illegal.
sentences.chinese: 日射纱窗风撼扉，香罗拭手春事违。

sentences.english: A ground level awning window with flyscreen accompanies each cooling pond.
sentences.chinese: 一楼的水平遮阳百叶窗与纱窗伴随着每个冷却池。

sentences.english: The house has been screened against mosquitoes.
sentences.chinese: 房屋已装上了纱窗纱门来防避蚊子。

sentences.english: Install screen door or screen window in your room.
sentences.chinese: 给房屋安装纱门和纱窗。

sentences.english: Insect screens shall be fitted to all windows that can be opened.
sentences.chinese: 所有能打开的窗户都应该有防虫纱窗且尺寸合适。

sentences.english: The high pressure control system and wires are integrated in the frame of dust-absorbing mesh window.
sentences.chinese: 高压控制系统与导线都集成在吸尘纱窗的框架内。

sentences.english: The sliding door flyscreen you advised is exactly what we are needing, thank you.
sentences.chinese: 你建议的推拉门纱窗，正是我们需要的，谢谢你。

definition: window/the opening panel of a window
cover of lamp/lampshade/glass cover of oil lamp
